    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_8570125" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/8570125" />
    <a title="Eddie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/198230-eddie"><img alt="Eddie" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/8570125?book_show_action=true">Nov 02, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eddie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eddie" href="/user/show/198230-eddie">Eddie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780767915809" href="/book/show/126260.The_United_States_of_Arugula">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer8570125" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18167502785960080175">This book started off incredibly slowly and dryly--talking about Julia Child and James Beard should be entertaining, and rollicking and crazy, but it wasn&apos;t. It picked up a LOT when the next generation started to come into the picture--maybe because the folks at Chez Panisse *were* in fact completely crazy in the first days. <br/><br/>Regardless, it really was fascinating--how *fast* we went from Julia Child hoping to sell a few books to McDonalds selling mesclun salads is almost incomprehensible. It&apos;s st</span>
  <span id="freeText18167502785960080175" style="display:none">This book started off incredibly slowly and dryly--talking about Julia Child and James Beard should be entertaining, and rollicking and crazy, but it wasn't. It picked up a LOT when the next generation started to come into the picture--maybe because the folks at Chez Panisse *were* in fact completely crazy in the first days. <br /><br />Regardless, it really was fascinating--how *fast* we went from Julia Child hoping to sell a few books to McDonalds selling mesclun salads is almost incomprehensible. It's still not clear what caused things to tip in that direction, nor is it clear if it's <br /> A) sustainable<br /> B) happening outside of the coasts.<br /><br />But the fact remains that you now can buy a bagel in Peoria, IL, and you couldn't 20 years ago.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="18167502785960080175" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


